UNITED STATES v. GREENWOOD DAIRY FARMS, Inc. No. 5417. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. April 12, 1935. For opinion below, see 8 F. Supp. 398. Val Nolan, of Indianapolis, Ind., for the United States. A. P. Smith, of Indianapolis, Ind., for appellee.

Before SPARKS, FITZHENRY, and ALSCHULER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
